            "text": "The MATH dataset (Hendrycks et al., 2021) contains 12,500 competition math problems across algebra, geometry, number theory, counting, probability, pre-calculus, and intermediate algebra — graded 1-5 by difficulty. AIME (American Invitational Mathematics Examination) provides 30 harder problems per year with integer answers 0-999, published annually by the Mathematical Association of America."
