      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Evaluating on MATH"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datasets import load_dataset\nimport anthropic, re\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\nmath_ds = load_dataset(\"hendrycks/competition_math\", split=\"test\")\n\ndef extract_boxed(text: str) -> str:\n    match = re.search(r\"\\\\boxed\\{(.+?)\\}\", text)\n    return match.group(1).strip() if match else \"\"\n\ndef solve_math(problem: dict, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\") -> str:\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=2048,\n        system=(\n            \"Solve the math problem step by step. \"\n            \"Put your final answer inside \\\\boxed{}.\"\n        ),\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": problem[\"problem\"]}],\n    )\n    return extract_boxed(resp.content[0].text)\n\ndef evaluate_math(n_samples=100) -> float:\n    problems = list(math_ds.shuffle(seed=42).select(range(n_samples)))\n    correct = 0\n    for p in problems:\n        pred = solve_math(p)\n        gold = extract_boxed(p[\"solution\"])\n        if pred == gold:\n            correct += 1\n    return correct / n_samples\n\n# Note: exact-match on LaTeX is strict; sympy equivalence checking gives\n# a more generous and accurate measure of mathematical correctness.\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sympy-Based Answer Equivalence"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import sympy\nfrom sympy.parsing.latex import parse_latex\n\ndef latex_equal(pred: str, gold: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if two LaTeX math expressions are symbolically equal.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        p = parse_latex(pred.strip())\n        g = parse_latex(gold.strip())\n        return sympy.simplify(p - g) == 0\n    except Exception:\n        return pred.strip() == gold.strip()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HotpotQA and MuSiQue: Multi-Hop Reasoning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-hop benchmarks require the agent to chain facts across multiple documents. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HotpotQA",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (Yang et al., 2018) provides 113k Wikipedia-derived questions where answering requires synthesizing two supporting passages. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MuSiQue",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (Trivedi et al., 2022) extends this to 4-hop reasoning chains with 2,417 tasks, and includes unanswerable variants to test the agent's ability to abstain."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datasets import load_dataset\nimport anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nhotpot = load_dataset(\"hotpot_qa\", \"distractor\", split=\"validation\")\n\ndef solve_hotpot(item: dict, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\") -> str:\n    # Build context from supporting facts\n    context_parts = []\n    for title, sentences in zip(item[\"context\"][\"title\"], item[\"context\"][\"sentences\"]):\n        context_parts.append(f\"[{title}]\\n\" + \" \".join(sentences))\n    context = \"\\n\\n\".join(context_parts)\n\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=256,\n        system=\"Answer the question using the provided context. Be concise.\",\n        messages=[{\n            \"role\": \"user\",\n            \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{context}\\n\\nQuestion: {item['question']}\"\n        }],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n\ndef exact_match(pred: str, gold: str) -> bool:\n    return pred.lower().strip() == gold.lower().strip()\n\ndef f1_score(pred: str, gold: str) -> float:\n    pred_toks = set(pred.lower().split())\n    gold_toks = set(gold.lower().split())\n    common = pred_toks & gold_toks\n    if not common:\n        return 0.0\n    precision = len(common) / len(pred_toks)\n    recall = len(common) / len(gold_toks)\n    return 2 * precision * recall / (precision + recall)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "StrategyQA and LogiQA: Commonsense and Formal Logic"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "StrategyQA",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (Geva et al., 2021) contains 2,780 yes/no questions that require implicit multi-step reasoning over world knowledge (e.g., \"Was Aristotle alive during the construction of the Colosseum?\"). "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LogiQA",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (Liu et al., 2020) provides 8,678 multiple-choice questions adapted from Chinese civil service exam logic sections, testing deductive reasoning with formal logical structures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datasets import load_dataset\nimport anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nstrategy_qa = load_dataset(\"wics/strategy-qa\", split=\"test\")\nlogiqa = load_dataset(\"lucasmccabe/logiqa\", split=\"test\")\n\ndef solve_strategy_qa(item: dict, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\") -> bool:\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=64,\n        system=(\n            \"Answer yes or no. Think step by step, then on the last line \"\n            \"write only 'yes' or 'no'.\"\n        ),\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": item[\"question\"]}],\n    )\n    text = resp.content[0].text.strip().lower()\n    last_line = text.splitlines()[-1].strip()\n    return last_line.startswith(\"yes\")\n\ndef solve_logiqa(item: dict, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\") -> int:\n    choices_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"{chr(65+i)}. {c}\" for i, c in enumerate(item[\"options\"])\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=256,\n        system=(\n            \"Read the passage and question, then choose the correct option. \"\n            \"Reply with only the letter (A, B, C, or D).\"\n        ),\n        messages=[{\n            \"role\": \"user\",\n            \"content\": (\n                f\"Passage: {item['context']}\\n\\n\"\n                f\"Question: {item['query']}\\n\\n\"\n                f\"Options:\\n{choices_text}\"\n            ),\n        }],\n    )\n    letter = resp.content[0].text.strip()[0].upper()\n    return ord(letter) - ord(\"A\")   # 0-indexed answer\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Chain-of-Thought Prompting Across Benchmarks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "All reasoning benchmarks benefit from chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting — instructing the model to reason step-by-step before giving the final answer. The improvement is largest on multi-step tasks (MATH level 5, MuSiQue 4-hop) and smallest on single-fact recall. Self-consistency (sampling multiple chains and taking the majority answer) further boosts accuracy on MATH by 5-10 percentage points."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef cot_solve(question: str, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\") -> str:\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=\"Think step by step. Show your reasoning, then give the final answer on a new line starting with 'Answer:'.\",\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": question}],\n    )\n    text = resp.content[0].text\n    for line in reversed(text.splitlines()):\n        if line.lower().startswith(\"answer:\"):\n            return line.split(\":\", 1)[1].strip()\n    return text.strip().splitlines()[-1]  # last line as fallback\n\n\ndef self_consistency(question: str, k: int = 5, model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\") -> str:\n    \"\"\"Sample k chains and take the majority answer.\"\"\"\n    answers = [cot_solve(question, model) for _ in range(k)]\n    return Counter(answers).most_common(1)[0][0]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmark Selection Guide"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
